race.comment: STRIDING BAY (5) brings a close second over 1600m at Launceston, enjoying the step-up in trip. He's on a 6-day return and will be hard to beat holding that form. I'M A MACHINE (2) has been within range here his last two and will appreciate the step up in trip. Has a handy 2kg claim today and the blinkers on for the first time. Expect him to be hitting the line hard. He has winning claims. ALPINE HONEY (1) finished a close third in the STRIDING BAY race when he led. May take a sit today and has winning prospects. KNIGHTS REIGN (3) is capable at best and keeps the handy 4kg claim. That brings him into it.
